<subSubSection lastPageId="52" lastPageNumber="53" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="51.[264,700,1644,1705]" box="[264,347,1679,1705]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<figureCitation box="[264,347,1679,1705]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–42" captionStartId="44.[264,383,1740,1764]" captionTargetBox="[268,1321,320,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-44@44.[267,1326,319,1725]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 32–42. Melaloncha spp., female, ovipositor, left lateral (except Fig. 40, bottom). Figures. 39 and 40 showing intersegmental membrane and sclerite of intersegment 7–8." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5070726" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5070726/files/figure.png" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Fig. 42</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[264,1322,1758,1905]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,421,1758,1784]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Recognition.</emphasis>
This species is easily recognized by the yellow body color and the setose lower lobe of the ovipositor.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="51.[264,1322,1758,1905]" lastBlockId="52.[264,1325,284,1230]" lastPageId="52" lastPageNumber="53" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,464,1838,1864]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Description.</emphasis>
Female (male unknown). Body length 1.5–2.0 mm. Frons yellow; bare of setulae except few along eye margin and, in many specimens, dorsally­directed pair in location of supra­antennal setae (particularly well developed in 
<typeStatus box="[1016,1124,284,310]" pageId="52" pageNumber="53">holotype</typeStatus>
); ocellar triangle darkened. Mean frontal width 0.44 head width, range 0.41–0.49. Medial furrow absent. Ocular and genal setae light brown. Flagellomere 1 basally white, mostly yellow; aristomeres 1–2 and base of 3 yellow; rest of 3 brown. Palpus white; palpal setulae black. Scutum yellowish­brown, in some specimens with posterolateral dark brown spot. Scutellum yellowish­brown, with anterorlateral round black spot. Pleuron yellowishbrown, except basalare dark brown. Legs yellowish­brown. Combined length of foretarsomeres equal in length to foretibia. Foretarsal claws recurved, with large basal lobe. Mean costal length 0.49 wing length, range 0.48–0.50. Halter yellow. Abdominal tergites yellow anteriorly, black posteriorly. Venter of abdomen yellow. Ovipositor yellow at base, mostly black; slightly ventrally curved, tubular, with longer ventral lobe than dorsal lobe; with scattered setae of medium length, except denser on ventral lobe
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
